    {
      "comment": {
        "id": "14af14f0-8f08-4752-9e0f-7103f31b1ee9",
        "created_at": "2025-03-24T21:43:47.233Z",
        "updated_at": "2025-03-25T04:08:38.040Z",
        "post_id": "c5669fc4-763f-4011-a109-b31485d5fb91",
        "user_id": 262197243,
        "body": "Gamma is not a bout creating support or resistance lvls...the primal effect is to swallow or expand volatility... add or decreaseliquidity. and SOMETIMES they act as support/resistance lvls... sometimes...but it depends on many more things... read my OD chat post. the effect thatcreates the magnetic effect is positive chamr convexisty in a MM shortbutterfly pattern. you have negative charm below the price and positive charmabove it. as expo comes, gamma increases, the speed profile becomes steeper inthe fly pattern, and the charm effect increases. negative charm below the highgamma strike makes dealers shorter delta, triggering buyback flow... but aboveit is positive charm that makes them longer delta, forcing them to sellfutures. the momentum gets locked up to that zone, and gamma pins it at the end,no espcape as high gamma counter- adjusments needed for algos whenever theprice wants to go up or down. But only if vol is low",
